            "body": "<p>It should be<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private String num;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>not<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private string num;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20012887,
            "question_id": 20012620
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7b6b2d846944082b5579d55d36221d6f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 1722376,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1577850,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1577850/simont",
                "reputation": 2398,
                "display_name": "SimonT",
                "accept_rate": 89
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1384572601,
            "creation_date": 1384570973,
            "body": "<p>The variables <code>tnum<\/code> and <code>num<\/code> are being declared both in the class <code>Phonekeypadpanel<\/code> and in the constructor.  When you try to assign values to them, you end up only changing a local copy residing in the constructor and not the class variables.  Change the line <code>String num = \"\";<\/code> into <code>num = \"\";<\/code> and change <code>JLabel tnum = new JLabel();<\/code> into <code>tnum = new JLabel();<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Finally, replace each <code>\"one\"<\/code>, <code>\"two\"<\/code>, etc. with <code>\"1\"<\/code>, <code>\"2\"<\/code>, etc. because when you put <code>System.out.println(event.getActionCommand());<\/code> at the top of <code>actionPerformed<\/code> you'll see the output is the label of the button.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20014117,
            "question_id": 20012620,
            "last_edit_date": 1384572601
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/w9jTN.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 3013228,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2587435,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2587435/paul-samsotha",
                "reputation": 209749,
                "display_name": "Paul Samsotha",
                "accept_rate": 88
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1384565453,
            "creation_date": 1384559491,
            "body": "<p>You're trying to use <code>e.getActionCommand()<\/code>, but there is no <code>e<\/code>, it should be <code>event<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>else if (event.getActionComand().equals(\"three\")){\n    ...\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>event<\/code> is tour <code>ActionEvent<\/code> variable, not <code>e<\/code>.  That's why the <code>can't find symbol<\/code>. Your just missing on the \"three\"<\/p>\n\n<p>And<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Jlabel display = new JLabel (\"Phone Number \");\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>No such class <code>Jlabel<\/code>. Should be <code>JLabel<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p><b>Edit:<\/b> To display text<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (event.getActionCommand().eqauls(\"three\")){\n    num += \"3\";\n    display.setText(num);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20012685,
            "question_id": 20012620,
            "last_edit_date": 1384565453
        }
